cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.MM

The paper discusses convolutional dictionary learning algorithms, which are commonly used in computer vision and image processing applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses optimization methods, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of masks for learning from incomplete data, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses computational cost, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
